<L>__{interior court building. morning.}
<A>__{truman enters the courtroom building. a crush of defendents, families, attorneys and police officers. truman goes to enter a courtroom but a security guard blocks his path.}
<C>__{security guard}
<D>__{you a witness?}
<C>__{truman}
<D>__{er, yes...}
<P>__{(suddenly losing heart)}
<D>__{no, no i'm not.}
<C>__{security guard}
<D>__{closed session.}
<A>__{before the guard can move him on. truman sneaks a look at proceedings through the courtroom door window. he recognizes the two youths sitting at the defendent's table. a prosecutor is on his feet, addressing the jury. meryl is working attentively at her stenotype machine, her fingers rapidly pressing the keys. however, truman notices a glaring omission. there is no paper emerging from meryl's machine. the roll of paper tape sits on the floor beside her chair leg.}
